@startuml Schalke
title Workspace App — V1 Layered Architecture (Components)

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false

package "UI Layer" {
  [GUI] as UI
}

package "AppOrchestrator Layer" {
  [IWorkspaceAppController] as CTRL
}

package "WorkspaceEngine Layer" {
  [CaptureService] as CAP
  [RecaptureService] as REC
  [RestoreService] as RES
}

package "Persistence Layer" {
  [IWorkspaceRepository] as REPO
  [SchemaMigrator] as MIG
}

package "Domain Layer" {
  [Workspace] as WS
  [ApplicationEntry] as AE
  [WindowLayout] as WL
  [OperationResult] as OR
}

package "WinApi Layer" {
  [IWindowEnumerator] as ENUM
  [IWindowCloser] as CLOSE
  [IProcessLauncher] as LAUNCH
  [IWindowMover] as MOVE
  [IMonitorService] as MON
}

UI --> CTRL : invokes use cases
CTRL --> CAP : orchestrates + progress
CTRL --> REC : orchestrates + progress
CTRL --> RES : orchestrates + progress

CAP --> ENUM : snapshot windows
CAP --> WS : builds models
CAP --> REPO : create(workspace)

REC --> ENUM : snapshot windows
REC --> WS : overwrite models
REC --> REPO : update(workspace)

RES --> REPO : get(workspace)
RES --> MIG : migrate(V1)
RES --> ENUM : enumerate windows
RES --> CLOSE : WM_CLOSE (sequential)
RES --> LAUNCH : launch(exePath)
RES --> MOVE : set bounds / minimize / activate
RES --> MON : clamp to visible area
RES --> OR : events + errors

REPO ..> WS : serialize/deserialize
WS --> AE
AE --> WL

note right of RES
  Restore flow (V1):
  1) Global close (sequential, abort-on-timeout)
  2) Launch each exePath
  3) Position up to N captured windows
  4) Replay z-order
end note

note bottom
  V1 constraints:
  - Windows-only
  - Visible top-level windows (not cloaked)
  - Shell infrastructure windows excluded (taskbar/desktop host)
  - Fully off-screen: clamp + minimize
  - Partially off-screen: clamp only
end note

@enduml
